### Why

During the 2026-05-16 PR sweep I encountered two new failure modes that share the same
search surface as v1.0.0 (PR-merge-blocked due to signing issues) but had distinct root
causes:

1. **GraphQL signature.state lag.** `gh pr view --json commits` returned UNSIGNED for
   31 commits across three PRs (Argus #520, Scylla #1978, Agamemnon #382) for 10+
   minutes after push, even though the REST `/commits/<sha>` endpoint immediately
   reported `verified=true reason=valid`. I wasted 30 minutes trying to re-upload the
   GPG key (which was already on the account â€” `gh gpg-key add` returned HTTP 422
   "subkey already exists") before realizing GraphQL was just lagging.

2. **gpg-agent pre-warm requirement in sub-agent shells.** I had initially assumed
   sub-agents needed explicit `-S` because GraphQL showed UNSIGNED. Actual root cause
   was the GraphQL lag (Learning A), but the investigation revealed that
   `commit.gpgsign=true` global config DOES propagate into sub-agent shells. The real
   gotcha is that sub-agent non-interactive subshells need `GPG_TTY` set AND a
   pre-warmed gpg-agent, or the signature silently fails to produce â€” indistinguishable
   from "config didn't propagate" when combined with the GraphQL lag.

Both learnings are diagnosed via the REST API, not by changing config.

